CM_ BU_ BCM_Gp "Body Control Module, Lear BCM Without TPMS and with HCM, Atlas 3R2

Node type - Type 3, OSEK, Local / Network wake-up 

This variant has 12 LIN bues";
CM_ BU_ DDM "Driver Door Zone Module Gen 2 - DDM_DZM2
";
CM_ BU_ DRDM "Driver Rear Door Zone Module Gen 2, DRDM_DZM2";
CM_ BU_ DSM "Generation 2 Driver Seat Module - DSM_Gen2 World Class Interior
";
CM_ BU_ FTCM "Folding Top Control Module    (FTCM)";
CM_ BU_ FTCMB "Folding Top Control Module B    (FTCMB)";
CM_ BU_ GWM "XCL Gateway Module for EVA2, NCR17Q4 / Feature Bundle 3 onwards
";
CM_ BU_ LPDM "Left Power Door Module.

Only on SVO programmes.";
CM_ BU_ PDM "Passenger Door Zone Module Gen 2- PDM_DZM2
";
CM_ BU_ PRDM "Passenger Rear Door Zone Module Gen 2 - PRDM_DZM2";
CM_ BU_ PSM "Generation 2 Passenger Seat Module - PSM_Gen2 World Class Interior
";
CM_ BU_ RFA "Remote Function Actuator";
CM_ BU_ RGTM "Rear Gate/Trunk Module";
CM_ BU_ RGTMB "Rear Gate/Trunk Module B";
CM_ BU_ RLSM "Generation 2 Rear Left Seat Module - RLSM_Gen2";
CM_ BU_ RPDM "Right Power Door Module.

Only on SVO programmes.";
CM_ BU_ RRSM "Generation 2 Rear Right Seat Module - RRSM_Gen2 World Class Interior

";
CM_ BU_ TBM "Tow Bar Module";
CM_ BU_ TSTR "Offboard Tester with High Speed Comfort CAN Interface - TSTR_HS";
CM_ BU_ VIM "Vehicle Immobilizer Control Module";
CM_ BU_ WDCM "Wireless Device Charger Module";
CM_ SG_ 66 ABSBrakeLightRequest "To request brake light activation for automatic braking functions in the ABS e.g. HDC, ACC, QA, IEB, AEBA, HDA etc.";
CM_ SG_ 66 ABSMILRequest "This signal is part of the OBDII functions. The ABS requests MIL functionality via the EMS. The EMS has the authority to over-ride ABS MIL requests.";
CM_ SG_ 66 EPBLongitudinalAcc "This is the measured Longitudinal Acceleration from the EPB.  When the vehicle is parked up-hill (noseup), the reading would be positive, when parked downhill (nosedown) then reading would be negative. On flat surface the reading would be '0' (zero).

Will permanently be set to 255? on Jaguar Dura PBM.";
CM_ SG_ 66 EPBMode "Current state of Electric Park Brake (EPB). State encoded.
All states are used by the Jaguar system.
States 0, 1, 3 shall be used by the Land Rover system.";
CM_ SG_ 66 EPBStatus "Summary of the mode that the Electric Park Brake is in.


";
CM_ SG_ 66 HillDescentMode "To inform ECM; TCM about actual HDC function status.";
CM_ SG_ 66 KeepNetInAfterRunABS "CAN signal stating if the network is required for After-Run.

Description of bit field detailing each application function to be stored in the DID (After-Run Function 1- 16):
b0: Vehicle Speed
b1: HEV Braking Function (Hybrid only)
b2 - b15: not used
";
CM_ SG_ 66 KeepNetInPreRunABS "CAN signal stating if the network is required for Pre-Run.

Description of bit field detailing each application function to be stored in the DID (After-Run Function 1- 16):
b0: HEV braking function
b1 - b15: not used
";
CM_ SG_ 66 ODORawCount "The true scaling factor of this signal is hardware dependant based on the rolling circumference (assumed and actual) and the number of teeth on the wheel speed sensor tooth ring.
ODORawCount does not indicate a default condition in the CAN signal. This may be determined from other signals e.g. WheelSpeedFrRQF and WheelSpeedFrLQF.

Rear Wheel Drive and AWD Vehicles (Jaguar X150/X250/X351/X152):
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Raw Rolling Count (counts through zero) of two front wheel speed signals. Measures distance travelled based on a reference circumference of 2.101m and a tooth ring of 46 teeth (AWD vehicles 48 teeth). Calculated by counting both the rising and falling edges of the raw sensor signals from the two front wheel speed signals. Signal increments on average in steps of 11.42mm (AWD vehicles 10.94mm).

Rear Wheel Drive and AWD Vehicles (Jaguar X760/X260/X761):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------";
CM_ SG_ 66 YawRate "This signal represents the yaw rate of the vehicle. The value of yaw rate is positive in a right (clockwise) turn.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSAliveCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSChecksum "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details
in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSEngVacReq "1 bit signal used to indicate that ABS is unable to generate any/ sufficient brake vacuum using the electric vacuum pump, and that the engine will need to generate brake vacuum itself.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSPwrTrnTorqReq "This is a renaming action for ABSReqEngRunning to give clarity of the intent of this signal.
It does not mean that the internal combustion engine must be running, rather it means that the powertrain torque must be available to the driver. This may be achieved by the internal combustion engine, or an e-machine, and the transmission";
CM_ SG_ 17 BrakePressure "Non Hybrid: The signal informs about the pressure in the master cylinder.
Hybrid: Indicates the pressure that would be present at the master cylinder for the same total
brake torque delivered by the HEV braking system compared to a conventional braking system.

Note: The signal saturates at 204.6 bar. The actual brake pressure can exceed 204.6 bar.";
CM_ SG_ 17 BrakePressureQF "Quality factor for the signal BrakePressure.
";
CM_ SG_ 17 VehicleSpeed "Use in conjunction with VehicleSpeedQF. A value of 65535d may also be set under error conditions.

Rear Wheel Drive and AWD Vehicles (Jaguar X150/X250/X351/X152/X760/X260/X761):
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VehicleSpeed is calculated as the average speed of the two driven rear wheels. If one wheel speed sensor fails, VehicleSpeed will use the speed information from the other sensor. Based on a rolling circumference of 2.101m on X150/X250/X351/X152. Based on a rolling circumference of 2.050m on X760. Based on a rolling circumference of 2.000m on X260. Based on a rolling circumference of 2.300m on X761.

Four Wheel Drive Vehicles (LandRover L319/L320/L322/L405/L494/L462):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VehicleSpeed is calculated as the average speed of all four wheels. In the case of wheel speed sensor failures, VehicleSpeed will use the speed information from the remaining sensors. ";
CM_ SG_ 17 VehicleSpeedQF "Quality factor for the signal VehicleSpeed. EuCD compliant signal.";
CM_ SG_ 1281 NMmessageBCMLS "This is the Network Management Protocol Data Unit (NMPDU) for the BCM on LS_CAN.

Description of station manager bit field detailing each application function (station manager function 1-16)
Bit 0 - Power Mode Management
Bit 1 - Start Warnings
Bit 2 - Courtesy Lights
Bit 3 - Alarm and Security
Bit 4 - Passive key scan requests
Bit 5 - Personalisation
Bit 6 - Doors and Windows
Bit 7 - Start Authorisation and ESCL
Bit 8 - Lighting
Bit 9 - Electric Park Brake
Bit 10 - Steering Column Control
Bit 11 - HeVAC
Bit 12 - Trip Computer Button
Bit 13 - Not Used
Bit 14 - Diagnostics
Bit 15 - Not Used

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);

";
