CM_ SG_ 421 BrakeLampOnStatus "This signal indicates the state of illumination of the brake lamps under driver braking and autonomous braking (i.e. by the DSC system). The signal reports whether at least one brake lamp is correctly responding to demands for illumination. It also reports a non-latching fault value if no lamps are responding correctly.

Signal encoding: Added in here as encoding description field not sufficient for text.

00 = One or more brake lamps successfully turned off in response to driver braking AND DSC braking requests to turn brake lamps off.

01 = One or more brake lamps successfully turned on in response to driver braking OR DSC braking requests to turn brake lamps on.

11 = None of the three brake lamps can be illuminated in response to driver braking OR DSC braking requests. This fault state does not latch - it is only reported while the fault state is present.";
