CM_ SG_ 424 ImmobiliserWarning "ImmobiliserWarning - Informs the user that the engine has not started due to Immobilisation not clearing. Feature of Start Auth to switch the ignition off if Immo Fails, with this in mind a warning will be present to inform user of failed reason.";
CM_ SG_ 424 ImmoNumberOfKeys "This signal shall be used to provide a number of keys display (service menu) and a warning to alert the user that additional keys have been added outside of JLR process, applies to additional keys only.";
CM_ SG_ 424 LoadSettings "To inform which Driver Id is currently active (bits 0-2).  
To inform if Remote Memory Recall is enabled (bit 7), if Reverse Mirror Dip is enabled (bit 8),if Easy Entry Exit is enabled (bit 9).


b0-b2:Not Personalized Driver and DriverId 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6;
   000 DriverId 0 (Not Personlized Driver)
   001 DriverId 1 
   010 DriverId 2
   011 DriverId 3
   100 DriverId 4 (FoE/LR only)
   101 DriverId 5 (LR Only)
   110 DriverId 6 (LR Only)
   111 Not used
b3-b15 , 1=Enable, 0=Disable
b3: Not Used
b4: EntSettings (Audio);
b5: NavSettings;
b6: ClimateSettings;
b7: PhysicalSettings (SeatAndMirrorForward);
b8: MirrorRearward;  (FoE, LR only); 
b9: EasyEntryEasyExit  (FoE, LR only); 
b10: HLA (FoE only); 
b11: ACCFCWSettings; 
b12: AutoTransmission (FoE only); 
b13: CCDSettings; (FoE only); 
b14: VehicleSettings (VCC), Steering Setup (FoE); 
b15: MenuBlocked (VCC), AutoFold (JLR);";
