CM_ SG_ 425 StealthModeStatus "Signal carrys feedback information about whether the stealth mode feature is currently enabled and whether the feature is currently active.

Functionality of stealth mode described in IPK eTracker   9750160
[Stealth_IPC_001]
Stealthmode in the IPC shall be 'enabled'/'disabled' by the 'StealthmodeStatus' MS_CAN message.

[Stealth_IPC_002]
Stealthmode in the IPC shall be deemed 'enabled' when the 'StealthmodeStatus' MS_CAN message conveys the value '1'.

[Stealth_IPC_003]
Stealthmode in the IPC shall be deemed 'disabled' when the 'StealthmodeStatus' MS_CAN message conveys the value '0'.

'Stealthmode' - 'Torchlight Effect' Interaction
-----------------------------------------------
{Reference: KFC 563 v6}

[Stealth_IPC_004]
The IPC shall turn ON the torchlight effect over-riding the (user's selection)/(torchlight effect feature manager's choice) when Stealthmode is deemed 'enabled'.

[Stealth_IPC_005]
The IPC shall restore control of the torchlight effect to the (user's selection)/(torchlig";
