CM_ SG_ 177 WiperWinterParkReq "Description of signal - This signal refers to the front wiper park position.  If set WiperWinterParkReq = 1 will result in the front wiper parking in an 'on-screen' position.  If WiperWinterParkReq = 0, will result in the front wiper parking in the 'off-screen' position.";
CM_ SG_ 108 IgnitionAuthDataControl "Authorise Ignition.

Byte 1 Definition: 
00=Idle, 
01=KeyStatus,
02 = Challenge Query 
03=Response, 
05=Enable Status.

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);
";
CM_ SG_ 110 IgnitionAuthDataTarget "Ignition Authorisation.

Byte 1 Definition:
01 = Idle
03 = Challenge Response
04 = Error Status.

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);
";
CM_ SG_ 318 AmbientLightValueIPC "This signal takes raw ambient light data from ambient light sensor located in instrument cluster and publishes it on the CAN Bus.
";
CM_ SG_ 318 DistanceToEmpty "Trip computer fuelled range function displayed value in kilometres only.
Used by:
1) Navigation function to compare journey length with available fuel and advise if there is
insufficient fuel for the journey.
2) VSC to calculate Combined Range (Fuel+EV).";
CM_ SG_ 318 InstAccEnable "This is used to inhibit cruise if the IC has not been programmed for ACC.";
CM_ SG_ 318 IPCAliveCnt "This signal is used by other ECU's to monitor the IPC. It will increment by 1 every 20ms. When the value of 15 is reached, it will reset to 0 on the next cycle";
CM_ SG_ 318 OdometerMasterValue "EuCD Signal.
Range: 0 - 16777214 (0-FFFFFEh)
Resolution: 1 KM
FFFFFFh = Invalid Data

                                                                         
NB: Signals greater than 16bits have to be of Signal Type (Bytes) as VSX does not support Unsigned signals >16bits.

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);



                             
";
CM_ SG_ 318 SpeedometerUnits "Indicates the main speedometer units. Intended for use by cruise control, ACC, ASL & ISL instead of TripUnits to set the units for setspeed.";
CM_ SG_ 318 SPMModeRequest "Indicates SPM sensitivity level request from driver via IPC.";
CM_ SG_ 318 StgColLockGndEnableStatus "Steering Column Lock Ground Enable Status";
CM_ SG_ 318 TPMSLoadThresholdsReq "Signal to transmit the vehicle load condition to TPMM";
