CM_ SG_ 97 ClutchPedalPressed "Reflects the 'clutch slightly engaged status'. Depending on the configuration of clutch inputs in the system this is either when the 25% switch indicates 'pressed', or when the linearized clutch position sensor value exceeds a threshold, possible to calibrate (e.g. approximately 25%). The 'clutch pressed' output signal shall be reset to 'released' when either the 25% switch indicates 'released', or when the linearized clutch position sensor value sinks below another calibratable threshold (i.e. hysteresis).";
CM_ SG_ 97 ClutchPedalSwitch "Informs when the clutch is pressed, at least, to a specified position.The switch indicates fully depressed, >75%, clutch pedal";
