CM_ SG_ 349 DZMPasLeftHmiOp "Used to convey BSM door mirror HMI state back to the BSM modules. Message Inactive indicates that the DZM has determined that its physical location is such that the status information is contained in the other signal (i.e. If driver left DZM then passenger left signal will contain 'message inactive')

DZMPasLeftHmiOp    3 bits
Type	Value	Scale	Offset	Interpretation
Logical Value	0	 	Message Inactive
Logical Value	1	 	HMI Fault
Logical Value	2	 	HMI not illuminated
Logical Value	3	 	HMI status LED illuminated
Logical Value	4	 	HMI alert LED illuminated
Logical Value	5-7                           Not used
";
CM_ SG_ 349 DZMPasRightHmiOp "Used to convey BSM door mirror HMI state back to the BSM modules. Message Inactive indicates that the DZM has determined that its physical location is such that the status information is contained in the other signal (i.e. If driver left DZM then passenger left signal will contain 'message inactive')

DZMPasRightHmiOp    3 bit 
Type	Value	Scale	Offset	Interpretation
Logical Value	0	 	 Message Inactive
Logical Value	1	 	 HMI Fault
Logical Value	2	 	 HMI not illuminated
Logical Value	3	 	 HMI status LED illuminated
Logical Value	4	 	 HMI alert LED illuminated
Logical Value	5-7                            Not used
";
