CM_ SG_ 1368 NMmessagePSM "Network Management Signal. This signal contains Network Management Data. This data includes the DA (Destination Address), CF (Control Field) and up to 6 data bytes of user defined data (currently not used by Jaguar).

Description of station manager bit field detailing each application function (station manager function 1-16)
Bit 0 - Passenger Seat Movement
Bit 1 - Memory Recall
Bit 2 - Memory Save
Bit 3 - Cancel Memory Recall
Bit 4 to Bit 15 - Unused 

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);

Refer 'Software Requirement Specification for CAN Network Management' (VCC doc no 31812308)

CAN ID:
X150/X250 - 0x528
GMRDB - 0x558";
