CM_ SG_ 191 CrashAirbagStatus "Driver and passenger airbag deployment status. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashOccClassStatus "Front passenger seat occupancy status. This information is to be considered while estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashPACOSSwitchState "'Passenger Airbag Cut Off Switch' state. This information is to be used while estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashPretensionerStat "Driver's and front seat passenger's pretensioner state. This information is used in estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSeatBeltBcklState "Driver's and front seat passenger's seatbelt buckle state. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSeverityClass "Crash severity classification for frontal collisions. Set to 'No event' for rear/side collisions.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSideAirbagStatus "Side airbags/curtains deployment status. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashStatusPIE "This signal defines the crash status of the PIE.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashStatusRCM "This signal defines the crash status of the vehicle safety system.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeFront "Signal indicates whether front crash has occurred or not. This is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No Front crash
1 - Front crash

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeRear "Signal indicates whether rear crash has occurred or not. This is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No rear crash
1 - Rear crash

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeRoll "Signal indicates whether vehicle rollover has occurred or not. This information is required to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.
";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeSide "Signal indicates whether side crash has occurred or not. This information is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No side crash
1 - Side crash 

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatBeltBcklError "When the bit is set to a '1', a fault condition exists for the driver's seat belt buckle switch.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatBeltBcklState "When the bit is set to a '1', the driver's seat belt buckle is latched.
This signal will be invalid and set to 1 (latched) during proveout and should not be used by subscriber until the valid state is established at 1sec post ignition on PM6";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatPositionError "Error status of driver seat track position switch.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatPositionStatus "Status of driver seat track position switch.

This signal will be invalid and set to 1 (forward) during proveout and should not be used by subscribers until the valid state is established at 1sec post ignition on (PM6)";
CM_ SG_ 191 KeepNetInAfterRunRCM "An after-run function master shall send a CAN signal stating that the network is required during after-run. This allows the after-run manager to keep the OSEK nodes awake in order to create a stable ring and also allows supporting slaves to continue CAN transmission or supply ECU power.";
CM_ SG_ 191 PassSeatBeltBcklError "When the bit is set to a '1', a fault condition exists for the passenger seat belt buckle switch.";
CM_ SG_ 191 PassSeatBeltBcklState "When the bit is set to a '1', the passenger seat belt buckle is latched.";
CM_ SG_ 191 PassSeatPositionStatus "This signal will be invalid and set to 1 (forward) during proveout and should not be used by subscribers until the valid state is established at 1sec post ignition on (PM6)";
CM_ SG_ 74 A1 "Beschleunigung 1 (Lateral Acceleration 1). Positive value when vehicle is in a left hand turn. Units of m/sec2.

See IMU bus spec. for details
";
CM_ SG_ 74 A1_STAT "Status Beschleunigung 1 (Lateral Acceleration 1 Status)

Indicates the status of the Lateral Acceleration 1 signal, A1: 
XXX1 = sensor element not populated 
XX1X = signal faulty 
X1XX = sensor initialising 
1XXX = sensor channel not calibrated 

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 74 CLU_STAT "Clusterstatus (Sensor Status). NOT SUPPORTED. Unused signal from standard IMU sensor signal set.

See IMU bus spec. for details
";
CM_ SG_ 74 CRC1 "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 74 MSG_CNT1 "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 74 PSIP1 "Gierrate 1 (Yaw Rate 1). Positive value when vehicle is in a left hand turn. Units of Grad/sec, 1 Grad = 1/400th of a full circle.

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 74 PSIP1_STAT "Status Gierrate 1 (Yaw Rate 1 Status).

Indicates the status of the Yaw Rate 1 signal, PSIP1:
XXX1 = sensor element not populated
XX1X = signal faulty
X1XX = sensor initialising
1XXX = sensor channel not calibrated

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 76 A2 "Beschleunigung 2 (Longitudinal Acceleration). Positive value when vehicle is accelerating forwards. Units of m/sec2. 

See IMU bus spec. for details
";
CM_ SG_ 76 A2_STAT "Status Beschleunigung 2 (Longitudinal Acceleration Status).

Indicates the status of the Longitudinal Acceleration signal, A2: 
XXX1 = sensor element not populated 
XX1X = signal faulty 
X1XX = sensor initialising 
1XXX = sensor channel not calibrated 

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 76 CRC2 "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 76 MSG_CNT2 "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 76 PSIPP1 "Gierbeschleunigung 1 (Yaw Angular Acceleration 1). NOT SUPPORTED. Unused signal from standard IMU sensor signal set.

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 76 PSIPP1_STAT "Status Gierbeschleunigung 1 (Yaw Angular Acceleration 1 Status). 

Indicates the status of the Yaw Angular Acceleration 1 signal, PSIPP1: 
XXX1 = sensor element not populated 
XX1X = signal faulty 
X1XX = sensor initialising 
1XXX = sensor channel not calibrated 

Set to XXX1 as PSIPP1 is not supported.

See IMU bus spec. for details";
CM_ SG_ 1288 NMmessageKVM "Network Management Signal. This signal contains Network Management Data. This data includes the DA (Destination Address), CF (Control Field) and up to 6 data bytes of user defined data (currently not used by Jaguar). 

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);

CAN ID:
X150/X250 - 0x508
GMRDB - 0x508

Description of station manager bit field detailing each application function (station manager functions)
Bit 0: LRN - Learn (FOB, TPMS, PK, etc)
Bit 1: ISM - Input Signal Manager
Bit 2: OSM - Output Signal Manager
Bit 3: ELM - E-Latch Manager
Bit 4: CMM - Configuration and Mode Manager
Bit 5: RMM - RFR Mode manager
Bit 6: DGN - Diagnostics
Bit 7: unused
Bit 8: ECI - EE Cache Interface
Bit 9: EDI - EE Direct Interface";
