CM_ SG_ 483 KVDecryptedMsg "Remote decrypted command from KVM.

Bit coded:
0000=IGNORE
0001=Lock
0010=Unlock
0011=Tailgate
0100=Approach Light
0101=Panic Alarm
0110=Security Check Req
0111=Change Lock Mode
Range 1000 - 1101 = Not used
1110 = Raise Suspension 
1111 = Lower Suspension 

Bit 4 Button Status: 0 = Not held, 1 = Button Held (Jaguar documentation only)
Bit 5-12 RSSI value
";
CM_ SG_ 483 PECentralLockCmd "Passive Entry lock/unlock request
";
CM_ SG_ 483 PELockButtonReq "Notification of lock button request with conditions incorrect";
CM_ SG_ 483 PKeyId "Passive Key ID

Each bit is assigned to a Key as follows:

Bit 0 = KeyID1  (0000 0001)
Bit 1 = KeyID2  (0000 0010)
Bit 2 = KeyID3  (0000 0100)
Bit 3 = KeyID4  (0000 1000)
Bit 4 = KeyID5  (0001 0000)
Bit 5 = KeyID6  (0010 0000)
Bit 6 = KeyID7  (0100 0000)
Bit 7 = KeyID8  (1000 0000)

This enables more than one Key to be present at a time.";
CM_ SG_ 483 PKeyIdScanArea "Reports where the passive key was found.

EuCD signal.

JLR note:
---------------
This signal should be grouped in RFA_Gp. However, it is not possible for EuCD to currently do this due to backward compatibility issues. For JLR 10MY it shall be ensured that this signal is written to at the same time as RFA_Gp and that this signal is packaged in the same CAN frame as RFA_Gp.";
CM_ SG_ 483 PKeyIdsInAreaReported "Reports how many keys that have been found for each key search.

