CM_ SG_ 503 EmergencyBrakingStatus "To enable the visible warning signal to warn other drivers that your vehicle is performing an emergency braking manoeuvre. This can be for example the hazard warning lights or flashing brake lights. These are turned on when the Emergency Braking Light (EBL) function is triggered, the triggering depending on the vehicle speed, deceleration and ABS activation.";
CM_ SG_ 503 FirstGearManual "Flag signal that indicates if the first gear is engaged or not. Manual transmissions only.";
CM_ SG_ 503 GSAPositionDisplay "Message used by IPK and ETS to display selected gear information.TCM will set multiple bits when e.g in Drive 5th gear and in Sport. The Signal TCMDrivingModeDisplay can be used for gear 1-8 display when in manual mode.

Init: Blank ETS display and Blank IPK display. Bit 14 and 15 set to 1, all other bits set to 0 (49152 decimal)

Bits 0 - 5: Gear Selection
000000 = Auto selection
000001 = 1st Gear
000010 = 2nd Gear
000100 = 3rd Gear
001000 = 4th Gear
010000 = 5th Gear
100000 = 6th Gear
100001 = 7th Gear
100010 = 8th Gear
100100 = 9th Gear

Bits 6 - 11: Gear Mode
000001 = Fault
000010 = Park Position
000100 = Reverse Position
001000 = Neutral Position
010000 = Drive Position
100000 = Sport Position

Bits 12 - 13: Flash Display
x1 = FLASH ETS Display
1x = FLASH IPK Display

Bits 14 - 15: Blank Display
x1 = Blank ETS Display
1x = Blank IPK Display";
CM_ SG_ 503 GSAPosStatus "Actual PRNDS Position of the vehicle Transmission (simplified version of GSAPositionDisplay)";
