CM_ SG_ 364 TCUDataControl "CAN signal transmitted by TCU requesting a feature from BCM. Signal is also used to send the 'auth challenge response' to BCM.

Telematics feature authorisation

Byte0 definition >> 01:Feature Request (TF2), 03:Challenge Response, 04:Error Status

AA BB
00 00 Idle
01 YY Determines feature requested (TF2)
 03 Alarm Reset
 05 Alarm Sensor Disable (Ferry Mode)
 0F Vehicle Location
 30 Pre-Requisite (EWuP)
 33 Remote Engine Stop
 56 Remote Engine Start
 68 Remote Vehicle Unlock
 6F Vehicle Secure
 73 Power up seat modules and desensitize internal motion sensors
 78 Power down seat modules and resensitize internal motion sensors
  All other values reserved for future use
03 R1 Challenge Response - R1 - R6 (6 byte ANS)
04 YY Error Status
 01 Error Status - Time Out
 02 Error Status - Target SID Not Stored
 03 Error Status - Engine Blocked";
CM_ SG_ 151 TCUDataTarget "CAN signal used by BCM to send 'auth challenge query' & request status to TCU
Telematics feature authorisation

Byte1 definition >> 02: Challenge Query, 05: Status

00  XX  Idle
02  C1  Challenge Query  - C1 - C6 (6 byte RN#)
05  81  Enable status = TCU Auth / Ok
01  Disable status = NOK (Target SID Not Stored)
01  Disable status = BLOCKED
01  Disable status = Challenge Error
XX - Don't Care
";
CM_ SG_ 1612 TESTRequestKVM "This signal is for configuring second TL channel in RFA. The second TL channel is very useful for debugging, testing and analyzing the system because it allows to pass selected data in near-real-time to the CAN where it can be captured by CANalyzer. These data are not needed for vehicle operation but are very useful for troubleshooting not only of the software but also of the vehicle systems problems.

Two frames are needed because of Volcano TL configuration requirements: a TL channel requires an input frame and an output frame. We are going to use output frame only. All other ECUs on the network should simply ignore these frames and their signals.

The frames and their signals should be very similar to TST_PhysicalReqKVM and TST_PhysicalRespKVM; the reason we want to avoid using these is to avoid interference with diagnostic layer.";
CM_ SG_ 1613 TESTResponseKVM "This signal is for configuring second TL channel in RFA. The second TL channel is very useful for debugging, testing and analyzing the system because it allows to pass selected data in near-real-time to the CAN where it can be captured by CANalyzer. These data are not needed for vehicle operation but are very useful for troubleshooting not only of the software but also of the vehicle systems problems. 

Two frames are needed because of Volcano TL configuration requirements: a TL channel requires an input frame and an output frame. We are going to use output frame only. All other ECUs on the network should simply ignore these frames and their signals. 

The frames and their signals should be very similar to TST_PhysicalReqKVM and TST_PhysicalRespKVM; the reason we want to avoid using these is to avoid interference with diagnostic layer.";
CM_ SG_ 949 TimeDateSetReq_ICM "Part    No of bits     LSB           MSB     Value range      Scaling    Offset     Max Hex   Invalid HEX
                              offset         offset     Min   ->   Max
Year         8             56              63        2000      2254       1         2000        0xFE          0xFF
Month      8             48              55          0            12         1             0          0x0C          0xFF
Day          8             40              47          0            31         1             0          0x1F          0xFF
Hour         8             32              39          0           23          1             0          0x17          0xFF
Minute      8             24              31          0           59          1             0          0x3B          0xFF
Second    8             16              23          0           59          1             0          0x3B          0xFF


Description                Size    Start bit     End bit    Unit of measure     Meaning
TimeAdjustRequest    ";
